The paper discusses a new model for memory management in modern operating systems, specifically for phones and server-based accelerators. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Operating Systems (cs.OS) category. The paper also addresses security issues related to memory management, which could place it in the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Systems and Control (cs.SY). The use of a formal model and executable specification in Haskell suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of Architecture (cs.AR) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
